President Donald J. Trump has accepted an invitation from the President of Poland, Andrzej Duda, to visit Poland before the G20 Summit in Germany. The purpose of the visit is to reaffirm the United States' commitment to Poland as a close European ally and to emphasize the Administration's focus on strengthening NATO's collective defense. The leaders will discuss bilateral and regional issues, with the goal of deepening the alliance based on shared values and interests. During his visit, President Trump will deliver a significant speech and participate in the Three Seas Initiative Summit to showcase the strong ties between the United States and Central Europe.